# ============================================================================
# PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: This is a PLACEHOLDER file for documentation only
#
# The REAL .env.production file MUST be manually created and maintained
# on the production server at:
#
#   ~/discovery.cfoeducation.it/backend/.env.production
#
# This file contains production secrets and credentials that should NEVER
# be committed to git.
#
# ============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT BEHAVIOR
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. The deploy script (deploy-on-server.sh) explicitly EXCLUDES .env.production
#    from rsync to preserve production credentials
#
# 2. During deployment, the script will:
#    - Check if .env.production exists on server
#    - Validate required variables are present
#    - Create .env from .env.production
#    - Fail deployment if .env.production is missing or invalid
#
# 3. To create .env.production on production server:
#
#    # Copy local file to server (FIRST TIME ONLY)
#    scp backend/.env.production user@server:~/discovery.cfoeducation.it/backend/
#
#    # Or manually create on server
#    ssh user@server
#    cd ~/discovery.cfoeducation.it/backend
#    nano .env.production
#
# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# ============================================================================
#
# The following variables MUST be present in .env.production:
#
# - DATABASE_URL              PostgreSQL connection string
# - JWT_SECRET                Secret for JWT token signing (NEVER change in production!)
# - ENCRYPTION_KEY            AES-256 key for 2FA (32 bytes hex)
# - JWT_2FA_SECRET            Secret for 2FA JWT tokens
# - CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID     R2 storage account ID
# - CLOUDFLARE_ACCESS_KEY_ID  R2 access key
# - CLOUDFLARE_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY  R2 secret key
# - EMAIL_USER                SMTP username
# - EMAIL_PASS                SMTP password/app password
#
# ============================================================================
# EXAMPLE STRUCTURE (use backend/.env.production.example as reference)
# ============================================================================
#
# NODE_ENV="production"
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/db"
# JWT_SECRET="your-production-jwt-secret-here"
# ENCRYPTION_KEY="your-32-byte-hex-encryption-key"
# PORT=3010
# FRONTEND_URL="https://discovery.cfoeducation.it"
# ... (see .env.production.example for full list)
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# If deployment fails with ".env.production not found":
#
# 1. The file is missing on the production server
# 2. Check backup directory: ~/backups/.env.production.backup_*
# 3. Restore from backup or upload new file
# 4. Re-run deployment
#
# See TROUBLESHOOTING.md for detailed recovery procedures.
#
# ============================================================================
